00:29:07.950 --> 00:29:10.860
So just staying on that,
because I'm glad you said that.

00:29:10.860 --> 00:29:13.470
And it's interesting that you
say that because my question

00:29:13.470 --> 00:29:14.880
was around the endgame.

00:29:14.880 --> 00:29:19.170
Because in the book, you
quote Frantz Fanon and say,

00:29:19.170 --> 00:29:21.480
"colonialism is not
a thinking machine,

00:29:21.480 --> 00:29:25.950
nor a body endowed with
reasoning faculties.

00:29:25.950 --> 00:29:27.810
It is violence in
its natural state,

00:29:27.810 --> 00:29:30.450
and it will only
yield when confronted

00:29:30.450 --> 00:29:32.010
with greater violence."

00:29:32.010 --> 00:29:35.040
So my question was, are
we headed to revolution?

00:29:35.040 --> 00:29:38.220
It sounds like you feel that
there is the opportunity

00:29:38.220 --> 00:29:39.630
for reconciliation.

00:29:39.630 --> 00:29:40.380
CHRIS HAYES: Yeah.

00:29:40.380 --> 00:29:43.330
I mean, I'm not--

00:29:43.330 --> 00:29:47.370
Fanon was speaking about a
specific context and generally

00:29:47.370 --> 00:29:54.210
a revolutionary and
places like Algeria.

00:29:54.210 --> 00:29:56.765
I think that the differences
between our situation

00:29:56.765 --> 00:29:58.890
and theirs are sort of more
salient in that respect

00:29:58.890 --> 00:30:02.670
than the similarities in
terms of the way forward.

00:30:02.670 --> 00:30:07.370
But the streets of
Baltimore felt revolutionary

00:30:07.370 --> 00:30:09.680
after Freddie Gray.

00:30:09.680 --> 00:30:13.112
And Ferguson felt revolutionary.

00:30:13.112 --> 00:30:14.320
There's a certain amount of--

00:30:14.320 --> 00:30:18.940
I mean, humiliation is a
particularly potent force

00:30:18.940 --> 00:30:23.170
driving human affairs because
the humiliated subject cannot

00:30:23.170 --> 00:30:28.060
act on their humiliation as
a definitional truth about

00:30:28.060 --> 00:30:30.480
humiliation.

00:30:30.480 --> 00:30:33.800
Being humiliated in the
moment means taking it.

00:30:33.800 --> 00:30:34.400
Right?

00:30:34.400 --> 00:30:37.840
The cop calling you a name
when they pull you over.

00:30:37.840 --> 00:30:39.860
Got to take that.

00:30:39.860 --> 00:30:43.772
So humiliation has an
ability to be bottled up,

00:30:43.772 --> 00:30:44.480
and then explode.

00:30:47.550 --> 00:30:52.960
The Arab Spring started over a
cop harassing a street vendor.

00:30:52.960 --> 00:30:55.020
This cop had harassed
this street vendor,

00:30:55.020 --> 00:30:57.410
Mohamed Bouazizi,
time and time again,

00:30:57.410 --> 00:31:00.580
who was selling fruit
without a permit.

00:31:00.580 --> 00:31:03.540
Eric Garner was selling
cigarettes that were untaxed.

00:31:03.540 --> 00:31:07.830
And eventually,
that fruit vendor,

00:31:07.830 --> 00:31:10.680
after being slapped by the
cop one day and yelled at,

00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:12.205
lit himself on fire in Tunisia.

00:31:12.205 --> 00:31:15.410
And that was the start
of the Arab Spring.

00:31:15.410 --> 00:31:20.570
So there is a kind of
powder keg to the experience

00:31:20.570 --> 00:31:25.030
of humiliation
that I worry about.

00:31:25.030 --> 00:31:28.790
I also, though, do think
that one of the things that's

00:31:28.790 --> 00:31:32.480
been interesting is as
polarizing as Black Lives

00:31:32.480 --> 00:31:35.000
Matter and protests have
been, public opinion

00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:39.440
has moved in their direction
really significantly, actually.

00:31:39.440 --> 00:31:40.230
It's interesting.

00:31:40.230 --> 00:31:42.320
It shows up in Pew, and
it shows up in Gallup.

00:31:42.320 --> 00:31:48.190
And this is true
among white Americans.

00:31:48.190 --> 00:31:52.610
Questions about how often
police mistreat people,

00:31:52.610 --> 00:31:56.430
their concern about
whether there's

00:31:56.430 --> 00:31:58.830
equal justice in the criminal
justice system, these

00:31:58.830 --> 00:32:01.650
have all moved in BLM's
direction in last year.

00:32:01.650 --> 00:32:05.670
So I think, actually, as brutal
as the backlash has been,

00:32:05.670 --> 00:32:08.740
and as much friction
as there is around it,

00:32:08.740 --> 00:32:11.560
it is actually moving public
opinion in the right direction.

00:32:11.560 --> 00:32:13.720
It can be hard to
see that at times.

00:32:13.720 --> 00:32:14.610
But it is moving in
the right direction.

00:32:14.610 --> 00:32:15.484
TORRENCE BOONE: Good.

